#content.l-main-column

  %section.block
    %i.block-icon.icon-info.icon-bg-default
    %h2.block-title Greenwire icons
    :markdown
      We use font-icons for these icons. The fonts live in the font folder. The pattern for including them is to add a class to the dom element. We often use a `<i>` for icons.
    .code
      :code
        # lang: css
         .icon-user
         .icon-login
  %section.block
    %i.block-icon.icon-info.icon-bg-default
    %h2.block-title Section icons
    %p These are the icons we use on Greenwire for visual aid to clarify sections and blocks.

  %section.cardbox
    - for icon in data.icons.section
      .cardholder
        .card.icon
          %i{:class => "icon-#{icon}"}
          %code #{icon}

  %section.block
